Reasoning: The paper deals with lambda calculus and techniques for proving beta-inconvertibility, which are topics typically studied in the sub-category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The use of Boehm Trees and their limitations suggest that the paper could also be relevant to Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Type Theory (cs.TL). The paper also introduces a refined discrimination method for lambda-terms, which could be of interest to researchers in the sub-category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the generation of fixed point combinators, which could be relevant to Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL).
